node.text:
Full legs workout 🔥Get your photos/videos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting runningterritory.com/feature 👉🏼the link is in our bio: @RunningTerritory 

We remain strong in our 21 days challenge! Today's training a bit varied, simple but demanding Full at the end💪🏽 remember that every day we are increasing the intensity in the routines.
4 set x 20 reps (with a 30-second pause between each exercise)

In the second exercise, hold it for 10sec at the end of the reps.

The last 3 exercises are in "super series" that's without a pause between each one, the rest is done only when the round is finished, which is a maximum of 45sec.

Let's go with everything! There is no result more beautiful than the one you achieved with sacrifice and effort 💪🏽

📹 @azuboughgouhnon

node.text:
Ultra running 🔥 Apply to promote your content in our account, go to our link in bio: @RunningTerritory

Ultra running was something I knew very little when I started ( First I just did Trekking... and then started with 10Km ) but I found a passion for running 🏃‍♀️ in the mountains 🏔, so I improved, and started to run longer and tougher distances 🤩
••
I really think that as you age, you find strength you didn’t know you had ... and this happened to me... In my 50’s I felt more confident and powerful than ever 🏃‍♀️💪🏻💪🏻
••
So my top tips to start  in trail running are...
1. Start we’re you are... from there you will improve
2. You are not old to start.. running is a sport for every age
3. Use the right shoes for you! Ones that are comfortable, and fit you well.
4. Regular strength work will help reduce the risk of injury, and help you get stronger.
5. Rest and recovery are the key to allow your body to rebuild between workouts. 
6. Have fun with your training and racing, if you take it to seriously, you will lose the simple joy of doing something you love❤️
I hope it helps you 🤩 have a great day wherever you are 😘” ~ Follow her for more.

📷 @frangibar

Jump rope 💦 Wanna see your content posted in our account? Apply for a feature on runningterritory.com/feature (link in my bio: @RunningTerritory)

Just shuffling my way around the mat again on this cold afternoon 🥶 I literally love shuffling with the jump rope - each week my shuffle post might look the same to you, but just with some different music. To me, my shuffles are getting cleaner, I’m increasing the bpm week on week and I’m getting more in to the rhythm of whichever song I’ve got on! I’m working my way up to incorporating some direction changes and releases too but that won’t be until 2021 ... baby steps!! ➡️ swipe for slow mo
📹 @skippingwithsarah

node.text:
Would you dare? 🙄 Wanna see your content posted in our account? Apply for a feature on runningterritory.com/feature (link in my bio: @RunningTerritory)

📷 @roberbargueiras

Drills 💪 Get your photos/videos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting runningterritory.com/feature 👉🏼the link is in our bio: @RunningTerritory

Everyone knows by now that im no fan of static stretching for warming up!

Instead, try using these drills to help ACTIVATE and STRENGTHEN your lower half; hips, knees, glutes, hamstrings, quads, ankles… all of it!

Also great for those wanting to improve their high kicks and general hip mobility, whilst building stability and single leg strength!

📝 Stay active and in control of your legs (and entire body) throughout. There’s a massive difference between being able to control your weight mid-air, and just throwing your leg up in the air and hoping for the best. 

Test yourself! If someone was to say HOLD IT, would you be able to stop in your position without falling over?

Give them a go and let me know what you think!👇

A1.)
▪️Lateral Leg Lifts
▪️10 Reps/Side

A2.)
▪️90-Degree Internal/External Hip Rotations
▪️4 Reps/Direction/Side

A3.)
▪️Forward Leg Swings (stop at knee)
▪️10 Reps/Leg

@phase6fitness

📽 @steph.rose.phase6
